Honda Halts China Parts Unit on Japan Quake, Business Daily Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-04T02:45:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/honda-halts-china-parts-unit-on-japan-quake-business-daily-says.html
Honda Motor Co. halted production at a
parts-making unit in  China  after the March 11 Japan earthquake
disrupted supplies, the National Business Daily reported today,
citing unidentified company workers.  Employees in Nanhai city in the southern province of
Guangdong were asked to go on leave from April 30 to May 15, the
Chinese newspaper said. May 2 was a national holiday in China.  Zhu Linjie, a Beijing-based Honda spokesman, said he wasnâ€™t
immediately able to comment on the report. The company halted
production at its two Chinese carmaking ventures from April 30
for scheduled inspections, he said.  --Tian Ying. Editors: Neil Denslow, Nicholas Wadhams  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
